In history written for such a purpose, the delineation of cha- racter, and analysis of actions into their motiveS, become the most important elements ; and it is plain that Tacitus desired in this part of his work to print indelibly on the memory of his readers the portraits of the ruling prince and of the minister whose rise and fall formed the most striking political events of the period.
